{
  "texts": [
    "This may also happen for particularly large problem instances [58].",
    "These capabilities will likely be above human-level performance in various tasks and domains, further complicating the monitoring and control of AI systems.",
    "For a general AI system, most of its capabilities can be considered surprising, as it is designed to adapt and learn from a wide range of situations.",
    "Anything non-deterministic in the AI system's behavior may lead to surprising outcomes, which pose challenges for monitoring and ensuring AI safety.",
    "By definition, emergent properties cannot be pre-detected, as they arise from complex interactions that are not explicitly encoded in the AI system's design."
  ]
}